    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-10T21:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-10-10T21:29:00-05:00" n="47"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d47">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.516/22: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-10T21:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 10, 1920—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 11—1:23 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Attention Norman Davis:</p>
                <p>Banco International suspended payments Saturday morning during which heavy runs
                    were made on Banco Nacional and Banco Español until regular closing hour.
                    President Menocal is said to be disposed to lend Government assistance, and
                    reported to have stated that this was opportunity for foreign banks to show
                    their favorable sentiments toward Cuba by cooperating to stop panic. Heads
                    foreign banks are still in session trying to decide what they might reasonably
                    recommend to their home offices. Government will tonight or tomorrow decree
                    fifty-day moratorium with several conditions. Depositors of $2,000 may withdraw
                    [10 or even 12 percent of] that amount. Further details tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
